Thierry Fremaux said he could not ban selfies at the Cannes Film Festival . 
  But he said celebrities will be discouraged from taking 'ridiculous and grotesque' pictures . 
  He said the pictures slowed down the event and caused problems for organisers . 
  Celebrities including Cate Blanchett and Michael Fassbender will not be allowed to take selfies . 
  17 films will be competing for prizes at the 68th festival in May . 
 